text.section:
The Council shall make recommendations regarding:
High quality professional development for teachers and principals regarding digital instruction or blending digital content with traditional classroom instruction;
Funding strategies to provide high quality, innovative options in course providers and delivery;
Student assessment and accountability;
Infrastructure necessary to support digital learning;
Mobile learning and mobile learning applications;
Aligning resources and digital learning initiatives of all State agencies;
Coordination of digital learning programs to prevent redundancy and inefficiency;
Planning for changes in technology and digital learning;
Expanded curriculum for mathematics, science, foreign language, and advanced placement courses;
Increasing education opportunities for at-risk, home-bound, special needs, and alternative education students; and
Implementation plans for providing digital learning opportunities to all students in the State
